  "title": "Adorable Dolls",
  "description": "Adds a delightful collection of interactive dolls to your world",
  "body": "<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"https://media.forgecdn.net/attachments/description/null/description_56e8954a-9f5a-439a-97b8-8c88ff7284c9.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"554\" height=\"66\" /></p>\n<p>Welcome to Adorable Dolls! This mod adds a delightful collection of interactive dolls to your world. You can change their appearance by renaming them, and engage in special interactions with these charming companions. Perfect for decoration and role-play, they are a charming addition to your builds and adventures.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>Core Features</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Customizable Dolls: </strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>A brand-new placeable doll block has been added to the game, featuring <strong>11 different poses</strong>. When held, the doll will perch cutely on your shoulder.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Skin Customization:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Use an anvil to rename the doll and change its appearance!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Special Interactions:&nbsp; </strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Special <strong>Supporters Dolls</strong> are included in the mod. By holding specific trigger items and right-clicking, you can activate exclusive animations for these dolls&mdash;a heartfelt thank you to our generous supporters.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Decorative &amp; Fun:&nbsp; </strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>These dolls can serve as cozy indoor decorations or become fun companions on your adventures, adding charm and personality to your builds and journeys.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>How to Use</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Obtaining a Doll:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can get dolls from the Creative or craft them.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Placing &amp; Interacting with Dolls:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Place the doll item in the world.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Crouch and right-click to change the doll&rsquo;s pose.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>- Hold an item and right-click to make the doll hold that item.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Changing Skins:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Use an anvil to rename the doll&mdash;the name determines its skin style. Try out different names to discover new looks!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Trigger Special Actions (Supporters Only) :</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 115%; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Hold a specific trigger item and right-click a supporters doll to activate its unique animation.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>Plans </strong></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mob Dolls&nbsp;</strong></li>\n<li><strong>More Animations</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>FAQ </strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Q: </strong>Why doesn&rsquo;t the skin change after renaming?&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>A: </strong>The name must be typed manually. Copy-pasted names or incorrect capitalization may not be recognized. Please check the supported name list below.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>Currently Supported Names</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Default Skins:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Steve</p>\n<p>Alex</p>\n<p>Ari</p>\n<p>Kai</p>\n<p>Noor</p>\n<p>Sunny</p>\n<p>Zuri</p>\n<p>Efe</p>\n<p>Makena</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Supporters Skins(A-Z):</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"border: none; width: 70.4724%;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 26.5709%; border: 1pt solid windowtext;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: normal; text-align: center;\"><strong>_TomatoFish_</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.5978%; border: 1pt solid windowtext; text-align: center;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: normal;\"><strong>Raw Cod</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 41.8312%; border: 1pt solid windowtext; text-align: center;\">\n<p style=\"line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"margin-left: -1px; width: 106px;\"><img src=\"https